4. Societal Over-Peak Dynamics
   - Many subsystems (population growth, land–resource stress, technological
     bonus) exhibit "over-peak" behavior: rising, reaching saturation, then
     entering diminishing returns.
   - Modeling over-peak transitions is crucial for long-horizon simulations.
   - This explains why certain civilizations collapse even after productivity
     has reached unprecedented heights.

5. The Great Singularity Conjecture
